    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.33) headline our offensive output. **Mickey Moniak** is the clear top play, benefiting from an incredible +19% SP skill boost against Roki Sasaki\u2019s high-xERA profile, coupled with a +14% park factor and the aggressive optimization of the #2 spot. Meanwhile, **Corbin Carroll** remains a core anchor; despite a tougher matchup against Kevin Gausman, his elite xwOBA (0.372) and the efficiency of the #2 hole in the order maintain his high floor. **Max Muncy** (71.26) also provides significant value, leveraging the same favorable matchup against Noah Schultz that elevates **Tyler Soderstrom** (68.86). We are leaning heavily into these high-variance, high-reward matchups against struggling arms to maximize our R and RBI totals.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was excluding **Alex Freeland** (53.79) from the final starting spots. While **Alex Freeland** offers a strong park boost, his projected #8 spot in the order acted as a drag on his efficiency score, keeping him just behind the more established volume of our primary starters. We also analyzed **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.31), but a negative platoon split against the southpaw Weathers made him a strictly bench-caliber play today. Risk management remains a priority; with several lineups still pending\u2014specifically for **Dalton Rushing**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, **Trevor Story**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Austin Riley**\u2014we are prepared to pivot if late scratches shift the order projections. Owners should note that the sub-60 scores for **Trevor Story**, **Brice Turang**, and **Jose Caballero** reflect the inherent difficulty of facing arms like Framber Valdez and Cole Ragans, but our commitment to SB remains the guiding principle in keeping **Brice Turang** and **Jose Caballero** active despite the challenging SP profiles.",
